text: Josef Jelínek (9 January 1941 – 29 November 2024) was a Czech footballer. He played as a forward. He made 10 appearances for the Czechoslovakia national team, scoring twice from 1961 to 1962."FOTBAL.CZ – Reprezentace A – statistiky". fotbal.cz. He was born in Prague, Protectorate of Bohemia and Moravia. Jelínek died on 29 November 2024 in Prague, Czech Republic at the age of 83. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:2024 deaths Category:Czech footballers Category:Sportspeople from Prague
